 Here's a JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII characters and their corresponding hexadecimal codes for the range of 0 to 7F:

```javascript
for (let i = 32; i <= 126; i++) {
    console.log(`Character: ${String.fromCharCode(i)} Hex: 0x${i.toString(16)}`);
}
```

This code uses the `String.fromCharCode()` method to convert the ASCII codes into characters, and then prints them along with their hexadecimal representation. The loop iterates from character code 32 (space) to 126 (~), which covers all printable ASCII characters.
